the ceremony shows that the \\\"tableau vivant\\\" (living painting) is based on \\\"The Feast of the Gods\\\" by Jan van Bijlert from 1635, which features \\\"Minerva, the goddess of wisdom, and Mars, the god of war, alongside Venus, the goddess of love, who is known for her well-known relationships.\\\"\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jan van Bijlert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\"}, {\"begin\": 2220, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minerva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8470534398099263e-33, \"text\": \"Minerva\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minerva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minerva\"}, {\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venus\", \"score\": 0.99769548282411, \"rank\": 0.002309840242297573, \"text\": \"Venus\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As per the historian, the act depicted during the ceremony shows that the \\\"tableau vivant\\\" (living painting) is based on \\\"The Feast of the Gods\\\" by Jan van Bijlert from 1635, which features \\\"Minerva, the goddess of wisdom, and Mars, the god of war, alongside Venus, the goddess of love, who is known for her well-known relationships.\\\"\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jan van Bijlert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\